{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-jsx","path":"/linux-file-permissions","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"file-permissions\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#file-permissions\" aria-label=\"file permissions permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>File Permissions</h1>\n<p>File permissions determine who can read, write, or execute a file. In Linux,\nthese details can be viewed by using the <code class=\"language-text\">ls -l</code> command. </p>\n<p>On the very left of the list, you will see text that looks similar to this:</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">-rwxrw-r--</code></p>\n<p>These are your file permissions.</p>\n<h2 id=\"what-do-these-code-classlanguage-textrwx-code-characters-mean\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-do-these-code-classlanguage-textrwx-code-characters-mean\" aria-label=\"what do these code classlanguage textrwx code characters mean permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What do These <code class=\"language-text\">rwx-</code> Characters Mean?</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">r</code> read - user is allowed to view the file's contents</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">w</code> write - user is allowed to edit the file's contents</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">x</code> execute - user is allowed to execute the file (or in the case of a directory, view its contents)</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">-</code> no permission - used in place when a permission is not granted</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"file-type\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#file-type\" aria-label=\"file type permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>File type</h2>\n<p>The very first character specifies the file type. In this case, <code class=\"language-text\">-</code> indicates a regular file. Different characters represent different types:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">b</code> block device</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">c</code> character device</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">d</code> directory</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">l</code> symbolic link</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">p</code> named pipe</li>\n<li><code class=\"language-text\">s</code> socket file</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"owner-groups-and-others\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#owner-groups-and-others\" aria-label=\"owner groups and others permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Owner, Groups, and Others</h2>\n<p>The next nine characters determine what permissions the owner, groups in ownership, and other users have.</p>\n<p>The first three characters after the file type indicate the ower's permissions. In <code class=\"language-text\">-rwxrw-r--</code>, the owner's file permissions are <code class=\"language-text\">rwx</code>. They are allowed to read,\nwrite, and execute the file.</p>\n<p>The following three characters determine permissions for members of groups that own the file. In this case, group permissions are <code class=\"language-text\">rw-</code>. They are allowed to\nread and write to the file, but cannot execute it.</p>\n<p>The last three characters are permissions for all other users that do not fit into the previous two categories. This example's permissions for other users are\n<code class=\"language-text\">r--</code>. They are only allowed to read the file.</p>\n<h2 id=\"diagram\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#diagram\" aria-label=\"diagram permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Diagram:</h2>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.comentum.com/images/permissions.jpg\" alt=\"diagram\"></p>","timeToRead":1,"excerpt":"File Permissions File permissions determine who can read, write, or execute a file. In Linux, \nthese details can be viewed by using the…","frontmatter":{"title":"Linux File Permissions","date":"2020-10-31 01:32:22 -0700","categories":["linux"],"tags":["linux","file permissions"],"description":null,"keywords":"linux, file permissions","author":"Calista Lai","cover":{"childImageSharp":{"fixed":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAABQAAAAPCAYAAADkmO9VAAAACXBIWXMAAAsTAAALEwEAmpwYAAAAZ0lEQVQ4y2Mw5v//n5qYYdRAODbiw60JnxwDPg2GvAhsBKP58BuK04UgzRai//9biUNoM2EIbSJAhgtBWJ/r/3831f//Yx3//4+w/v8/yvb//2i7//+tJSCWDbyXqRopNDFwNOsRjQHOdKSa6R2eoAAAAABJRU5ErkJggg==","width":540,"height":400,"src":"/static/18b0edfdfa96fadbadd7955f1202cbd7/819a5/linux.png","srcSet":"/static/18b0edfdfa96fadbadd7955f1202cbd7/819a5/linux.png 1x"}}}},"fields":{"slug":"/linux-file-permissions","date":"2020-10-31T08:32:22.000Z"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/linux-file-permissions","nexttitle":"Solving Project Euler's Problem 2 with Python","nextslug":"/solving-project-eulers-problem-2-with-python","prevtitle":"Localization and Internationalization","prevslug":"/localization-and-internationalization","tagList":["abstraction","OOP","Class","java","collection","API","Map","HashMap","LinkedHashMap","TreeMap","Python","cli","args","argparse","javascript","es6","beginner","codenewbie","Primary_key","implementation","Composite_key","language-support","localization","internationalization","linux","file permissions","Project Euler","Algortithms","SQL","database","commands","GO","Datatypes","Variables","Constants","HTML5","Web development","tricks","NumpPy","array","python","NLP","libraries","text processing","go","golang","data-structure","optimization","java 7","Java 8","comparison","mkdir(make-dir) and rmdir(remove-dir command) command","nodejs","backend","frontend","postgres","mac","installation","games","gamedev","memory","html","boots